@SG_ML_TITLE SingCorrect Tutorial
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
&#9;SingCorrect allows SGEXTN input fields (subclasses of @SG_ML_L008014SGWInput../cppclass/sgwinput) to autocorrect LaTeX style commands to the corresponding Unicode character. This is highly customisable and you can call @SG_ML_L03F05CSGWCustomisationPageControl::enableSingCorrectCustomisationPage../cppclass/sgwcustomisationpagecontrol#static_void_enableSingCorrectCustomisationPage_func_ to show the customisation page to the user.
&#9;SingCorrect works by detecting the SingCorrect prefix in user input and replacing every command found with the correct character. By default, the prefix is SG-\
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
&#9;For example, the below text
@SG_ML_WARN SG-\triangle ABC SG-\sim  SG-\triangle DEF
&#9;will become
@SG_ML_WARN △ABC ∼ △DEF
&#9;when typed into any SGEXTN input field.
&#9;In addition to LaTeX, all superscripts, subscripts, and even Optical Answer Sheet bubbles are supported by SingCorrect. For example,
@SG_ML_WARN SG-\SGoaszero SG-\SGoasfive SG-\SGoasfive SG-\SGoastwo SG-\SGoasfour SG-\SGoasF SG-\SGhome
&#9;would be corrected to
@SG_ML_WARN ⓪⑤⑤②④Ⓕ͸
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
&#9;All characters that SingCorrect can generate are guaranteed to have support in the SingScript.sg font.
&#9;
